/*
ี์อออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออ
ณ FUNCTION BUNGEE()                             *new*
ฦออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออออ
ณ
ณ  Short:
ณ  ------
ณ  BUNGEE() Mouseable, multi-level dropdown menu with triggers
ณ
ณ  Returns:
ณ  --------
ณ  NIL
ณ
ณ  Syntax:
ณ  -------
ณ
ณ  BUNGEE(<nTop>,<nLeft>,<nRight>,<aMenu>,[aColumns],;
ณ         [aColors],[aHotMice],[aHotKeys],[bExitCheck],;
ณ         [lImmediate],[lDropped],[nHideLevel],[nShadowPos],;
ณ         [nShadowAtt],[lHandleAlt] )
ณ
ณ  Description:
ณ  ------------
ณ  Creates and activates a dropdown menu (bungee style)
ณ
ณ  <nTop>          Row of menu bar
ณ  <nLeft>         Left side of menu bar
ณ  <nRight>        Right side of menu bar
ณ  <aMenu>         A menu definition array of arrays
ณ
ณ                  You  use the BUNGEE() menu array definition functions:
ณ                  BUNGSTART(), BUNGEND(), BUNGOPTION(),BUNGDROP(),
ณ                  BUNGUNDROP() together to create a menu definition array
ณ                  for BUNGEE( ). This basically defines the menu options,
ณ                  boxes and actions
ณ
ณ  [aColumns]      An array of columns to determine the column
ณ                  positions for the top bar options. Optional, as
ณ                  this is automatically determined otherwise.
ณ
ณ  [aColors]       An array of seven elements describing 6 colors
ณ                  and the box drawing frame string
ณ
ณ                  BACKGROUND COLOR         1
ณ                  SELECTED OPTION COLOR    2
ณ                  UNSELECTED OPTION COLOR  3
ณ                  INACTIVE OPTION COLOR    4
ณ                  SELECTED TRIGGER COLOR   5
ณ                  UNSELECTED TRIGGER COLOR 6
ณ                  BOX FRAME STRING         7   (as in "ฺฤฟณูฤภณ ")
ณ
ณ                  Defaults are extracted from the current
ณ                  values in SETCOLOR(), and adjusted to
ณ                  account for trigger letters and inactive
ณ                  colors.
ณ
ณ
ณ  [aHotMice]      An array of hot areas where, should the
ณ                  mouse click, a codeblock will be evaluated.
ณ                  The array is an array of arrays, where each
ณ                  sub-array is in the form:
ณ                      {nTop,nLeft,nBottom,nRight,bCodeblock}
ณ                  Where nTop..nRight refer to the screen
ณ                  coordinates of the hot area.
ณ                  i.e.
ณ                  @24,0 say "<Help>"
ณ                  aHotMice := { {24,0,24,5,{||dohelp}}  }
ณ
ณ
ณ  [aHotKeys]      An array of hotkey values, which, if one of
ณ                  the keys is pressed, a codeblock will be
ณ                  evaluated on the spot.
ณ                  The array is an array of arrays, where each
ณ                  sub-array is of the form:
ณ                      {nASCIIValue,bCodeblock}
ณ
ณ                  @24,0 say "<Help>"
ณ                  aHotKeys := { {K_F1,{||dohelp()}  }  }
ณ
ณ
ณ  [bExitBlock]    This is a codeblock which returns a LOGICAL
ณ                  which is evaluated before a menu exit is
ณ                  allowed. If it returns .f., a menu exit will
ณ                  not be allowed.
ณ                  i.e. {||MESSYN("Really exit?")}
ณ
ณ  [lImmediate]    Do mouse clicks or hot keys on options other
ณ                  than current option cause an immediate action
ณ                  request? Default = True
ณ
ณ  [lDropped]      Should the menu start up in dropped mode (boxes
ณ                  are already dropped from top bar) Default is
ณ                  True.
ณ
ณ  [nHideLevel]    This indicates the level to which the menu hides
ณ                  itself when executing an option action, a mouse
ณ                  hot button or a hot key.
ณ                  0 - does not hide itself at all
ณ                  1 - hides everything except the top bar  (default)
ณ                  2 - hides everything
ณ
ณ  [nShadowPos]    Optional shadow position for menu dropdown boxes.
ณ                  Valid options are:
ณ                       1. Lower left
ณ                       3. Lower right
ณ                       0. None
ณ                  Upper left and upper right shadow positions are not
ณ                  allowed. (they can overwrite parts of the menu bar)
ณ                  Default is SLS_SHADPOS(), unless SLS_SHADPOS() is
ณ                  upper left or upper right (7,9), in which case it
ณ                  is set to 0 (none).
ณ
ณ                  To force no shadows for the menu, pass 0.
ณ
ณ                  Boxes may not always have shadows, if the shadow would
ณ                  be drawn offscreen.
ณ
ณ  [nShadowAtt]   Numeric shadow attribute. Default is SLS_SHADATT(), whose
ณ                 default is 8. (grey on black)
ณ
ณ  [lHandleAlt]   Allow ALT+trigger letter combinations (ALT-A through ALT-Z)
ณ                 to select menu options
ณ
ณ  Examples:
ณ  ---------
ณ
ณ  (Also see S3META2.PRG in the sample files for a good example)
ณ
ณ  bungstart()
ณ  bungoption("Files")
ณ  bungdrop()
ณ          bungoption("Open" ,{} ,{||!lFileIsOpen} )
ณ          bungoption("Close",{||nil},{||lFileIsOpen } )
ณ  bungundrop()
ณ  bungoption("Edit")
ณ  bungdrop()
ณ          bungoption("DBF"  ,{||nil},nil )
ณ          bungoption("Ascii",{||nil},nil )
ณ  bungundrop()
ณ  bungoption("Quit",{||bungeequit()},nil)
ณ
ณ  aMenu := bungend()
ณ
ณ  @24,0 say "[ALT-X=exit]"   // set up Alt-X as a hotkey exit also
ณ  aHotKeys := { {K_ALT_X,{||bungeequit()}           }
ณ  aHotMice := {  {24,0,24,11,{||bungeequit()}     }  }
ณ
ณ  bungee(0,0,79,aMenu,nil,nil,aHotMice,aHotKeys, { ||messyn("Exit now?") }   )
ณ
ณ  Example 2
ณ  ---------
ณ
ณ  bungstart()
ณ  bungoption("Next",{||dbskip(1)})
ณ  bungoption("Prev",{||dbskip(-1)})
ณ  bungoption("Edit",{||doedit()})
ณ  bungoption("Add ",{||doadd()})
ณ  bungoption("Delete",{||dodelete()})
ณ  bungoption("Table",{||editdb(.t.)})
ณ  bungoption("Search")
ณ       bungdrop()
ณ       bungoption("Field Search",{||searchme()} )
ณ       bungoption("Key Search",{||SPOPSEEK()} )
ณ       bungoption("Query ",{||query()} )
ณ       bungundrop()
ณ  bungoption("Memo")
ณ       bungdrop()
ณ       bungoption("View",{||viewmemo()} )
ณ       bungoption("Edit",{||editmemo()} )
ณ       bungundrop()
ณ  bungoption("Hardcopy")
ณ       bungdrop()
ณ       bungoption("Record",{||hcrecord()})
ณ       bungoption("Memo",{||hcmemo()})
ณ       bungundrop()
ณ  bungoption("Quit",{||bungeequit()},nil)
ณ
ณ  aMenu := bungend()
ณ  bungee(0,0,79,aMenu)
ณ
ณ
ณ
ณ  Notes:
ณ  ------
ณ  Notes: Dropdown boxes will adjust for 'too far right' or 'too far down',
ณ  but there is no adjustment for 'too many options in the box to fit on
ณ  screen'
